deck: A Spanish illustrator who has worked in Spain, America, Germany, and Britain for various publishers.
description:
Demetrio Sánchez Gómez was born in the town of Pilar de la Horadada in the southeast of Spain. He has worked as the inker of the artists Jordi Franch and of Fuentes Man on El Hijo de Tarzán. In the 1960s he furthermore made series like La Conquista de la Luna in Información and Grago in La Verdad. He was also present at publishers like Bernabéu and Dalmau Socias with comics like Agente Secreto del CIA and Tumac.

He has worked extensively for the foreign market. For the American publisher Charlton he has illustrated romance, war, ghost, and western stories through the Union Studio. His work has also appeared in Bastei Verlag's Gespenster Geschichten in Germany.

From the 1990s on he has mainly worked for the British market.
name: Demetrio Sánchez Gómez

deck: A Guatemalan-born actor best known for his dramatic roles in films like Inside Llewyn Davis.
description:
Biography

Oscar Isaac is an Guatemalan American actor and musician. Born in Guatemala, in 1979, Isaac was raised in Miami Florida. Isaac has often referenced the trouble he would get into at school citing a penchant for amusing fellow classmates whilst earning the ire of teachers

Isaac was named as one of the "100 Most Influential People in the World." in Time magazines 2016 edition.

Acting Profile

Oscar Isaac is has starred and appeared in many critically praised film and television stories. Of note Inside Llewyn Davis, The Bourne Legacy, Ex Machina, Star Wars: The Force Awakens, X-Men: Apocalypse. Future roles include Star Wars: Episode VIII.

Comic Related Roles

Poe Dameron

Oscar Isaac will portray Resistance fighter pilot Poe Dameron in Star Wars: The Force Awakens, the seventh chapter in the Star Wars saga. The J.J. Abrams directed film is set for release December 18, 2015.

Apocalypse

Isaac stars in X-Men: Apocalypse as the titular villain. The 2016 film is directed by longtime director of the X-Men franchise, Bryan Singer.
name: Oscar Isaac

deck: Mario J. Lucero, Heaven Sent Gaming's cofounder, is the writer and co-creator of Reverie, Karis, Thad's World Destruction: Before Destruction, BladeChick, Mouton, and Koki'o Shade and Monkey.
description:
Early years

Born in Albuquerque, New Mexico on June 8, 1988. He was raised as the middle child, between two sisters, to father Haracio was a cowboy and mother Cathleen was a working class woman. After elementary school he was raised by his grandfather Joe and grandmother Toni, his grandfather was a retired trucker and his grandmother was a homemaker. He attended high school at Sandia View Academy, where he met his future business partner and wife Isabel Ruiz.

Career

Mario Lucero is an alumni, of computer science in design, from Collins College. He was part of a small game dev team called Our Own Little Coo, his and Isabel's branch of it was called Heaven Sent Gaming. After leaving college in 2007, he became an independent web designer. Starting in 2009 he began to work on several publications with Heaven Sent Gaming from multiple media formats, including music, websites, and comics.

Private Life

Mario is a singer/songwriter that performs electronic rock and country music.

He maintains a blog on Tumblr.
name: Mario J. Lucero

deck: Isabel R. Lucero, Heaven Sent Gaming's cofounder, is the artist and co-creator of Reverie, Karis, Thad's World Destruction: Before Destruction, BladeChick, Mouton, and Koki'o Shade and Monkey.
description:
Early life

Born Isabel Ruiz in Albuquerque, New Mexico on March 30, 1989. She was raised as the youngest child, the only daughter, to father Ismael a teacher and mother Maria a teacher with a masters degree. She attended private education throughout her entire education. She attended high school at Sandia View Academy, where she met her future business partner and husband Mario Lucero.

Career

Isabel R. Lucero is an alumni, of computer science in art, from Collins College. She was part of a small game dev team called Our Own Little Coo, her and Mario's branch of it was called Heaven Sent Gaming. After leaving college in 2007, she became a waitress while furthering her art career. Starting in 2009 she began to work on several publications with Heaven Sent Gaming from multiple media formats, including music, websites, and comics.

Private life

Isabel is an artist, and this goes beyond her plethora of artwork she creates for her comics.

She maintains a blog on Tumblr.
name: Isabel R. Lucero
